{
  "text": "A significant advantage of the procedure is that the flap allows performing CXL while keeping the epithelium of the cornea intact. From a patient's perspective, keeping the epithelium is associated with less pain and discomfort and better visual function during recovery period compared to epithelium debridement before CXL. Further, corneal sensitivity was shown to recover much faster (7 days compared to 3 months) when the epithelium was not removed [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "625890"
